                                                                    </div>
                                                <div id="content-body" class="row-fluid content-body"> <div class="region region-content clearfix">
  <div id="block-system-main" class="clearfix block block-system">       <div class="content"> <article id="node-3169" class="node node-stanford-page clearfix" about="/advising/make-appointment" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">      <span property="dc:title" content="Make an Appointment" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>    <div class="content">
    <div id="node-stanford-page-full-group-s-postcard" class="postcard group-s-postcard field-group-div"><div id="node-stanford-page-full-group-s-postcard-content" class="postcard-content group-s-postcard-content field-group-div"><div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><h2>How to Make an Appointment</h2>
<ul><li>To schedule an appointment with a <span>UAR</span> advisor, call (650) 723-2426 or visit the first floor in Sweet Hall.  Regular business hours are from 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. during the week, with the exception of Thursdays, which are from 12:00 p.m. to 5:00 p.m.  Note that appointments are scheduled for future dates; appointments cannot be scheduled for same-day meetings.</li>
	<li>Students who wish to meet with a Sweet Hall academic advisor are encouraged to call (650) 723-2426 to schedule an appointment.  Note that the Sweet Hall Advising Team is comprised of general and specialized advisors that include Pre-Professional (pre-health, pre-law, pre-education, pre-business), Transfers, Returning Students, Coterminal Students, Research &amp; Fellowships, Pre-Major Advising, and Progress &amp; Policy.
		<ul><li><strong>For quick ten-minute questions, students can visit Sweet Hall for drop-in advising during the following times:</strong>
				<ul><li>Mondays from 12:30 to 2:00 p.m.</li>
					<li>Tuesdays - Fridays from 1:00 p.m. to 2:00 p.m.</li>
					<li>Sign-ups begin at 12:00 p.m.</li>
					<li>Duration of Drop-in Advising Meetings:  10-minute meetings only; students needing additional time will be encouraged to schedule a longer appointment with their advisor, if necessary</li>
				</ul></li>
		</ul></li>
	<li>Drop-in advising may also be offered by Academic Advisors for Student-Athletes and Academic Directors.  See postings at their respective locations for current drop-in advising hours.</li>
</ul><h2>Fellowship and Pre-Professional UAR Advisors in Sweet Hall</h2>
<ul><li><strong>Fellowships and Scholarships:</strong>  Vivienne Fong</li>
	<li><strong>Pre-business Advisor:</strong>  Sally Mentzer</li>
	<li><strong>Pre-education Advisor:</strong>  Sally Mentzer</li>
	<li><strong>Pre-law Advisor:</strong>  Kathy Wright</li>
	<li><strong>Pre-med Advisors:</strong>
		<ul><li>Patricia Lewis</li>
			<li>Kathy Wright</li>
			<li>Yunny Yip</li>
		</ul></li>
</ul><h2>Transfer and Returning Students Advising in Sweet Hall</h2>
<ul><li><strong>Sally Mentzer</strong></li>
</ul><h2>Coterminal Advising in Sweet Hall</h2>
<ul><li><strong>Dennis Bogusz</strong>: <a href="mailto:dbogusz@stanford.edu" rel="nofollow">dbogusz@stanford.edu</a> or 650.723.1670<br />
		Prospective and current coterminal students may contact Dennis Bogusz directly to make an advising appointment.<br />
		Coterminal drop-in advising sessions will be available on Wednesdays from 1:00 – 3:00 PM in Sweet Hall, 1st Floor, during Winter Quarter 2015.</li>
</ul><h2>UAR Academic Advisors for Student-Athletes in the AARC</h2>
<p>Varsity Athletes who would like to make an appointment with a UAR Academic Advisor for Student-Athletes can call UAR at (650) 723-2426 or contact the advisors directly to schedule an appointment:</p>
<p><strong>Allison Vendt:</strong> <a href="mailto:avendt@stanford.edu" rel="nofollow">avendt@stanford.edu</a> or (650) 723-1176 or <a href="https://avendt.youcanbook.me/" rel="nofollow">Make an Appointment</a><br /><strong>Austin Lee:</strong> <a href="mailto:austindlee@stanford.edu" rel="nofollow">austindlee@stanford.edu</a> or (650) 723-3164 or <a href="https://austindlee.youcanbook.me/" rel="nofollow">Make an Appointment</a><br /><strong>Hillary McKinney:</strong> <a href="mailto:hmck@stanford.edu" rel="nofollow">hmck@stanford.edu</a> or (650) 725-0790 or <a href="https://hmck.youcanbook.me/" rel="nofollow">Make an Appointment</a><br /><strong>Melissa Schellberg</strong>:<a href="mailto:mschell@stanford.edu" rel="nofollow"> mschell@stanford.edu</a> or (650)723-5806 or <a href="https://mschell.youcanbook.me/" rel="nofollow">Make an Appointment</a><br /><strong>Solomon Hughes:</strong> <a href="mailto:syhughes@stanford.edu" rel="nofollow">syhughes@stanford.edu</a> or (650) 723-9650 or <a href="https://syhughes.youcanbook.me/" rel="nofollow">Make an Appointment</a></p>
